4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp, designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists even without any prior knowledge. The program focuses on building a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills to secure these environments. Students will also learn cloud security, penetration testing, and cyber threat intelligence analysis.

The bootcamp has a duration of 16 weeks, with 3 live online classes per week. Class sizes are kept small, with a maximum of 16 people. Upon completion, students receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate, which is recognized by multiple institutions.

No previous experience is required to enroll in the program. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560.

